On Mon, 7 Nov 2005, Don Tuleja wrote:

>What's the average temp in FL? Around 75-80 right? What's your engine's
>operating temp? Quite a bit higher. The less time an engine spends at
>something other than its operating temp, the cleaner it will run, the
>longer it will last.

My Porsche mechanic told to never warm up a car by letting it idle.
The quickest way to warm up the engine is to start driving it..not hard.
Letting an engine idle keeps the engine out of its operating temp too
long and you get more wear.

